            </div>

        </div>
    </section>


    <section class="design-system-section panel-inverse panel--wide">
        <div class="grid-width">
            <h3 class="design-system-headline" id="sign-posts">Sign posts</h3>
            <p>The sign post appears at the top of each page, it’s purpose is to inform the user about what page they are on. Imagine you are a broker and you have have 10 tabs open with 10 different quotes active at the same time. The sign post informs the user that they are on the correct client’s quote.</p>
            <p>The contents of the sign post are as follows:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Name of insurance product, e.g. Online Errors &amp; Omissions</li>
                <li>Name of the applicant (if available)</li>
                <li>Name of the current page, e.g. Application or Quote</li>
                <li>State of the quote or policy, e.g. Quote or Policy</li>
                <li>The reference number for the quote or policy</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </section>


